The paper deals with the problem of timely message delivery in IoT networks, which is a key issue in the field of networked systems and communication. The paper uses tools from stochastic geometry and queueing theory to model the network, which suggests that it belongs to the sub-categories of networked systems (cs.NI), information theory (cs.IT), and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the effect of traffic load on the performance of the network, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.MA) and performance analysis (cs.PF).
